cs.RO, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG. 

This paper focuses on using humanoid robots and neural networks to construct models for understanding the mechanisms of body representations. The use of robots suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO), while the use of neural networks suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of self-organizing maps (SOM), which are commonly used in neural network research and could fall under cs.NE. Additionally, the mention of tactile and proprioceptive inputs suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and sensory processing.
